I blew Go\'92s smoke back to its owner. \'91It\'92s our anniversary today. Five years.\'92\
\
\'91Wow.\'92 My sister cocked her head back. She\'92d been a bridesmaid, all in violet \'96 \'91the gorgeous, raven-haired, amethyst-draped dame,\'92 Amy\'92s mother had dubbed her \'96 but anniversaries weren\'92t something she\'92d remember. \'91Jeez. Fuck. Dude. That came fast.\'92 She blew more smoke toward me, a lazy game of cancer catch. \'91She going to do one of her, uh, what do you call it, not scavenger hunt\'97\'92\
