That one turned out to be the Alice in Wonderland statue at Central Park, which Amy had told me \'96 she\'92d told me, she knew she\'92d told me many times \'96 lightened her moods as a child. I do not remember any of those conversations. I\'92m being honest here, I just don\'92t. I have a dash of ADD, and I\'92ve always found my wife a bit dazzling, in the purest sense of the word: to lose clear vision, especially from looking at bright light. It was enough to be near her and hear her talk, it didn\'92t always matter what she was saying. It should have, but it didn\'92t.\
